<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN">
<html>
<head>
<title>Help: Changing the status of an order</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<link href="../style.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
</head>

<body>
<p class="titlebold">Changing the status of an order</p>
<p class="text">To change the status of orders:</p>
<ol>
  <li class="text"> Click on View under the Orders section in the main manager
    menu. </li>
  <li class="text">Select the search criteria for the orders you want to view
    and click the &quot;View Orders&quot; button. </li>
  <li class="text">Select the checkbox to the left of each order you want to
        change the status of. </li>
  <li class="text"><span class="text">Choose the sta</span>tus to change the orders to from the menu at
        the top right of the list of orders and press the Go button. </li>
</ol>
<p class="text"><strong>Note: Orders will generally appear on a different page
    once you change their
status.</strong></p>
</body>
</html>
